      <section id="sect-00003">
      <title>Adverse Effects and Contraindications</title>
      <para id="para-00009">Adverse effects of calcium channel blockers include dizziness, constipation, palpitations, fatigue, flushing, nausea, rash, headache, and swelling in the legs and feet. Serious side effects include thrombocytopenia, hypotension, and hyperglycemia. Clients with a hypersensitivity to calcium channel blockers or their components should not use this classification of drug. Other contraindications include sick sinus syndrome (except in clients with an artificial pacemaker), severe hypotension, a history of myocardial infarction, or a history of pulmonary congestion.</para>
